<p>I have a simple rails nested attributes params, I would like to know if there is a possibility to add my own value before update/create. like in the line :</p>  <pre><code>:approved_terms_time =&gt; DateTime.now  def post_params   params.require(:post).permit(:title, :content, user_attributes: [:id, :approved_terms, :approved_terms_time =&gt; DateTime.now]) end </code></pre>  <p>I certainly can do so in the Create \ update:</p>  <pre><code>@user.approved_terms_time = DateTime.now </code></pre>  <p>But I would like to know whether there is a more elegant way :)</p>